race.comment: Tough for the Derby hopefuls. ARABIAN PRINCE (7) goes on top. He's only had two runs to date but the return in the Listed Super Impose was excellent, getting a mile out his ground and flashing home to finish a narrow fifth. He'll relish 2000m, just where he gets to on the tighter track around Caulfield is the slight niggle. ENGINE OF WAR (5) was just edged out in the Derby Preview at Flemington last time out with OPTIONS (who had interference) back in third. Fancy there's little between them, as is the case for MIEWA (2) who started $3.40 in the Super Impose and went down by the barest of margins. He's another looking for this trip. AUTUMN MYSTERY (3) won the Derby Preview and has to be considered as well.
